sequenceDiagram
    participant P as Participant
    participant Sig as Signaling (WS)
    participant SFU1 as SFU (local)
    participant SFU2 as SFU (remote, cascade)
    participant O as Other Participants

    Note over P,O: Join meeting -> media publish + forward (simulcast)
    P->>Sig: WS connect + join {meeting_id, jwt}
    Sig->>Sig: validate JWT, check waiting room
    Sig-->>P: SFU endpoint + ICE creds + roster
    P->>SFU1: WebRTC offer (DTLS-SRTP)
    SFU1-->>P: answer + ICE candidates
    Note over P,SFU1: UDP media channel established
    par publish simulcast
        P-)SFU1: RTP low (180p) + med (480p) + high (720p+) + audio
    and forward to peers
        loop for each receiver
            SFU1-)O: forward stream at appropriate layer
            Note over SFU1: active speaker -> high; thumbnails -> low
        end
    end
    alt cross-region participant
        SFU1-)SFU2: cascade forward (SFU-to-SFU)
        SFU2-)O: forward to remote-region peers
    end
    O-)SFU1: TWCC feedback (loss, RTT)
    SFU1-)P: bandwidth estimate -> sender adjusts bitrate
    P->>Sig: mute / raise hand (control)
    Sig-)O: roster update
